name: Governor John Carney
tweet: This Christmas Eve I’m thinking about all the nurses, child care workers, correctional officers, grocery store clerks, educators and all those first responders and frontline workers who got us through this year.   Let’s follow their lead, do our part, and crush this virus.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: We look forward to seeing students back in classrooms in a hybrid format in January. I thank our schools for all the work they are doing to bring children back safely.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: We are pleased to make this funding available to districts and charter schools to ensure no staff members are laid off because of enrollment declines during the pandemic.  https://t.co/DDmnEj7jN6

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Our educators, school personnel, and school leaders have taken on the challenges of this pandemic and ensured children remain fed, educated, and supported.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Please stay vigilant. Wear a mask. Keep your distance.  For ideas on how to celebrate virtually and to stay connected this holiday season, visit  https://t.co/ljwwQYsJFW

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: With the winter surge of COVID-19 cases and hospitalizations we are facing, it’s important that we adjust our holiday plans. I know it’s tough, but we need to keep our holiday celebrations small and celebrate with only those in our immediate households.  https://t.co/Zf0q8HqPPh

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: It’s clear that cases and hospitalizations spiked after Thanksgiving gatherings.  We can’t afford another spike this Christmas. #MaskUpDE  https://t.co/IIIWR98yT5
